      <p> 
         This is an easy cabbage salad that kind of reminds me of Burmese Tea Leaf salad- good side dish with Indian/Asian flavors.
      </p>


  <title>Recipe</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:400,700|Playfair+Display:400,700" rel="stylesheet">  
</html>
<body>
  <div class="recipe">
    <div class="recipe--column">
      <div class="label">Recipe</div>
      <h2 class="title">Cabbage Salad</h2>

      <img class="recipe--img" src="https://place-hold.it/400x500" />

      <section class="section">
        <div class="hint">Ready in <strong>10 minutes</strong></div>
        <div class="hint">Serves <strong>4 people</strong></div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Tips</h3>
        <div>
          You can add chopped serrano chillies or jalapenos to this if you want it spicier. This goes great with Indian or Thai food.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="recipe--column">
      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 medium cabbage</li>
          <li>2 medium tomatoes</li>
          <li>1 small Persian cucumber</li>
          <li>1/4 cup peanuts</li>
          <li>2 tablespoons lemon juice</li>
          <li>2 tablespoons finely chopped cilantro (opt)</li>
          <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>

        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Preparation</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Shred the cabbage as as finely as you can. You'll need about 4 cups.
          </li>
          <li>
            Dice tomatoes and cucumber. 
          </li>
          <li>
            Roast the peanuts on medium heat till fragrant. Toss in pan often to prevent burning.
          </li>
          <li>
            Chop or grind peanuts into a crumble in a mortar and pestle.
          </li>
          <li>
            Mix the shredded cabbage with the juice of a lemon. Add the tomatoes and cucumbers.
          </li>
          <li>
            Add in the crushed peanuts, as well as (optional) cilantro and chopped chillies.
          </li>
          <li>
            Season the with salt and pepper and give a final mix.
          </li>

        </ol>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>


</body>
